UNOA.name: UN/ECE level A
UNOA.desc: As defined in the basic code table of ISO 646 with the exceptions of lower case letters, alternative graphic character allocations and national or application-oriented graphic character allocations.

UNOB.name: UN/ECE level B
UNOB.desc: As defined in the basic code table of ISO 646 with the exceptions of alternative graphic character allocations and national or application-oriented graphic character allocations.

UNOC.name: UN/ECE level C
UNOC.desc: As defined in ISO/IEC 8859-1 : Information technology -Part 1: Latin alphabet No. 1.

UNOD.name: UN/ECE level D
UNOD.desc: As defined in ISO/IEC 8859-2 : Information technology -Part 2: Latin alphabet No. 2.

UNOE.name: UN/ECE level E
UNOE.desc: As defined in ISO/IEC 8859-5 : Information technology -Part 5: Latin/Cyrillic alphabet.

UNOF.name: UN/ECE level F
UNOF.desc: As defined in ISO 8859-7 : Information processing - Part 7: Latin/Greek alphabet.

UNOG.name: UN/ECE level G
UNOG.desc: As defined in ISO/IEC 8859-3 : Information technology -Part 3: Latin alphabet No. 3.

UNOH.name: UN/ECE level H
UNOH.desc: As defined in ISO/IEC 8859-4 : Information technology -Part 4: Latin alphabet No. 4.

UNOI.name: UN/ECE level I
UNOI.desc: As defined in ISO/IEC 8859-6 : Information technology -Part 6: Latin/Arabic alphabet.

UNOJ.name: UN/ECE level J
UNOJ.desc: As defined in ISO/IEC 8859-8 : Information technology -Part 8: Latin/Hebrew alphabet.

UNOK.name: UN/ECE level K
UNOK.desc: As defined in ISO/IEC 8859-9 : Information technology -Part 9: Latin alphabet No. 5.

UNOX.name: UN/ECE level X
UNOX.desc: Code extension technique as defined by ISO 2022 utilising the escape techniques in accordance with ISO 2375.

UNOY.name: UN/ECE level Y
UNOY.desc: ISO 10646-1 octet without code extension technique.
